The trailer features Blake Lively as Lily Bloom, a woman who falls in love with Ryle Kincaid, played by Justin Baldoni. The film promises to be an emotional rollercoaster, as Lily struggles to navigate a complex and traumatic relationship amidst Ryle's unpredictable behavior. The trailer also features a song by Taylor Swift, adding to the film's highly anticipated release.

name: Tiger Woods
summary: Tiger Woods began the 2024 PGA Championship with a 1-over 72, placing him 10 strokes behind the early leaders. Despite his score, Woods expressed optimism about his chances of turning back time at the Valhalla Golf Club, where he won a historic duel nearly two decades ago. While declining to acknowledge a specific question, Woods' response suggested his focus on the present and his determination to prove himself once again. The Asian-born golfer who broke the record for becoming the first to win a men's major is dubbed the "Tiger Killer." Tiger's large gallery at this tournament highlights his continued popularity and the anticipation surrounding his performance.

name: Megalopolis
summary: Francis Ford Coppola's "Megalopolis," a long-gestating urban epic, has premiered at the Cannes Film Festival. Despite its grandiose ambition, the film has garnered mixed reactions. Critics describe it as "totally nuts" (Vulture), with its unbounded scope and unusual storytelling techniques. Despite the chaotic nature of the film, many praise its captivating visuals and Coppola's bold vision. Its release is expected to be limited, with plans for an IMAX release in select cities and a potential U.S. distribution deal still being negotiated. Despite its unconventional nature, some reviewers find hope and inspiration in Coppola's unbridled creativity, suggesting that "Megalopolis" may represent a new path for filmmaking.

summary: Warren Buffett's Berkshire Hathaway has disclosed a significant investment in Chubb, an insurance company. The investment, valued at $6.7 billion, has caused a surge in Chubb's stock price. name: Colorado Avalanche
summary: The Colorado Avalanche are struggling to adjust after forward Valeri Nichushkin was suspended for six months, just one hour before their playoff loss to the Dallas Stars. This suspension, announced pre-game, has been met with shock and disappointment by Avalanche players, who are now trying to fill the void left by Nichushkin. The suspension has had a significant impact on the team, as they were counting on Nichushkin to be a key contributor in the playoffs. The Avalanche are now trying to forge ahead without him, but it will be a challenge, as the Stars have taken control of the series after winning Game 3 with a defense-first strategy. The Avalanche will look to turn things around in Game 5, but it will be an uphill battle without Nichushkin, who has been a key part of their success this season.
